SIMPLE: rely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rely
<hw>Re*ly"</hw> <pr>(r?-l?")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Relied</conjf> <pr>(-l?d")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Relying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> +
<ets>lie</ets> to rest.]</ety> <def>To rest with confidence, as when
fully satisfied of the veracity, integrity, or ability of persons, or of
the certainty of facts or of evidence; to have confidence; to trust; to
depend; -- with <xex>on</xex>, formerly also with
<xex>in</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go in thy native innocence; <qex>rely</qex>⟦br⟧
On what thou hast of virtue.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On some fond breast the parting soul <qex>relies</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To trust; depend; confide; repose.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remade</ent>⟦br⟧
